<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="644" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.7111/14</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Rumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AWW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Andrews</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Jassy</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-22">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 27, 2.20 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>122. The Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me that the Roumanian King
                            intends sending to Washington as Minister Dr. <persName corresp="#p_AC1">Constantin Anghelescu</persName>, former Minister of Works, Deputy,
                            and professor of the University at Bucharest. He asks his acceptance by
                            the American Government. He would appreciate receiving a reply as soon
                            as possible.</p>
                        <p>I personally know Dr. <persName corresp="#p_AC1">Anghelescu</persName>
                            quite well. He is a man of good reputation, very well thought of,
                            intelligent and agreeable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Andrews</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>